# This installs on top of English Ubuntu: Ubuntu Studio, retaining Unity, while adding Taiwan Chinese, desktop management, and all verbist geek tools
## It may also work on top of English Ubuntu-GNOME
# Make this file executable with: chmod +X vubuntu-studio
# Run as sudo ./vubuntu-studio

add-apt-repository "deb http://archive.canonical.com/ $(lsb_release -sc) partner"
add-apt-repository -y ppa:pbek/qownnotes
apt-get update && apt-get -y upgrade && apt-get -y install \
## Basic tools for _ubuntu
rar unrar zip git vim guake guake-indicator kate dolphin vlc qownnotes clementine amarok docky filezilla thunderbird firefox chromium-browser flashplugin-installer djview-plugin unity-chromium-extension midori calligraauthor scribus sigil stellarium nautilus-dropbox skype grabc
## Ubuntu specific
mousepad thunar thunar-archive-plugin phatch thunar-media-tags-plugin \
## Ubuntu Studio
ubuntustudio-audio ubuntustudio-audio-plugins ubuntustudio-graphics ubuntustudio-photography ubuntustudio-publishing linux-lowlatency ubuntustudio-video \
## Ubuntu specific desktop
ubuntustudio-wallpapers unity-tweak-tool compizconfig-settings-manager xscreensaver rss-glx ubuntu-restricted-extras

## Final instructions:
echo "All is installed!

Add to startup:
sh -c \"sleep 10 && xscreensaver -no-splash &\"
fctix
guake OR guake-indicator (not both)

Screensaver instructions: (must make the mod as root after starting xscreensaver settings once)
nano /usr/share/doc/rss-glx/README.xscreensaver
sudo nano ~/.xscreensaver

Themes:
download from ubuntuthemes.org
mkdir ~/.themes
Unzip themes to ~/.themes/
Manage via Unity Tweak Tool

Chinese input:
1. Regional/language settings (let it update/fix language support)
 > Keyboard input method: fctix
 > Install/Remove Languages... (Chinese - Traditional)
 * Check regional formats (lots of confusion: systems and novice programmers make assumptions about this)
2. Add "fcitx" to starup programs (in addition to any fcitx-??? already in startup)
3. Run: Fcitx Configuration > Input Method > + (Add) > [uncheck Only Show Current Language] > Chewing (Chinese - Taiwan)
4. Restart"

